Today i learned about text processing commands in Linux.
##Commands practiced:
-sort : used to arrange lines alphabetically or numerically.
-sort -r : reverse sorting.
-sort -n : numeric sorting.
-uniq : removes duplicate lines from sorted output 
-uniq -c : counts repeated lines
-wc : counts lines,word, characters in and characters inin a file.
 I also practiced combining commands using pipes(|) for efficient text processing.
